    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Air Compressor and Power Steering/Fuel Pump -
        Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s06.2">
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, read all safety instructions in the "Safety Information"
                        section of this manual.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled before removing
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, remove ground cable from negative terminal of main
                        battery before disconnecting or connecting electrical components. Always connect ground cable
                        last.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not let engine fluids stay on your skin. Clean skin
                        and nails using hand cleaner and wash with soap and water. Wash or discard clothing and rags
                        contaminated with engine fluids.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <regulation>
                    <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel, and coolant) may be a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose
                        of engine fluids according to applicable regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, on
                        the ground, in sewers or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </regulation>
                <regulation>
                    <para>Dispose of fuel according to applicable regulations in a correct container clearly marked
                        DIESEL FUEL.
                    </para>
                </regulation>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to the Engine Electrical sections for information on removal of components prior to this
                        section.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc id="s06.2.1" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Air Compressor</title>
            <figure id="f3450006003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM16/M16100.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Oil supply hose fitting nut</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen oil supply hose fitting nut and disconnect hose from air compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450006004" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM16/M16101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air compressor coolant hoses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant return hose</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant supply hose</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hose clamp (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two hose clamps and disconnect air compressor coolant hoses.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450006005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM16/M16103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air compressor to bracket rear bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 45 bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove M10 x 45 and M10 x 30 air compressor to bracket rear bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450006006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM16/M16104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air compressor to bracket front bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air compressor bracket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two M10 x 30 air compressor to bracket front bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, get help when removing or installing the air
                        compressor.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard air compressor gasket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
